  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Application Structure**\n\nOkay, I\'m shifting gears. I was about to dive into component creation, but I realized I need a bird\'s-eye view. Now I\'m focusing on the application\'s structure. First, I will look at the layout. I\'m visualizing a minimalist header with typography that will evoke a gallery aesthetic.\n\n\n**Visualizing Component Integration**\n\nI\'m now integrating component visuals. I\'m focusing on \"EB Garamond\" for headings, large negative space, and simple indicators. I will include a stats bar with aggregate metrics and a streamlined \"Upload Artwork\" button. The filter/search section will use minimalist chips, and artwork previews will feature custom mats and borders with status badges. Finally, I\'m thinking of the upload canvas and the single artwork workspace.\n\n\n**Simulating Framed Artwork**\n\nI\'m now deep into the artwork simulator. I can visualize custom mats and frames\342\200\224natural oak, charcoal metal, walnut, even gold outlines! It\'s super premium. I have a specs overlay showing dimensions and style. The configuration form will let me edit title, notes, and select style, frame, mat, dimensions, and artwork status. Finally, I\'m thinking about a big \"Approve\" button.\n\n\n**Finalizing Output and Exports**\n\nI\'m finalizing the workspace\'s features. I will update artwork status to \"Approved for Production\" with a success indicator. I\'m adding \"Download High-Res Original,\" and \"Download Certified Mockup\" for an authentic representation, including simulated framing, matte card borders, SKU, and specs. An \"Export Spec Sheet (TXT)\" option saves detailed layout data. Lastly, there will be a \"Delete\" button, protected with confirmation. I will now create `/src/utils/canvasExporter.ts` to implement this. I will build an exporter that creates a `<canvas>` element. I will draw a thick border for the Frame and then a high-contrast white fill.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 21
      nanos: 625318176
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
