    thinking: "**Appreciating New Resources**\n\nI\'m quite impressed with the Canvas production spec sheet generator. The framing is aesthetically pleasing, and I particularly like how it seamlessly manages custom padding. The inclusion of technical labels like client, SKU, and dimensions is elegant, and the \"APPROVED FOR PRODUCTION\" stamp is a nice touch. It seems like a very useful tool, offering a rich feature set.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Visuals**\n\nI\'m now diving into the component design. I\'m focusing on the `/src/components/ArtworkFramePreview.tsx`, envisioning an interactive 3D/ambient preview that simulates frame and matting selections with high fidelity CSS. This will be a key element for the user. I\'m also planning the `/src/components/Header.tsx`, with the display title, statistics, and search, alongside the `/src/components/UploadModal.tsx`, a minimalist upload dialog. I am focused on low-contrast outlines and soft shapes, with desaturated golds or reds where appropriate.\n\n\n"
