      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFoC3HdMFn69mBn1tvRjz2-weihWvlX__X_CYtHID4TlbN_kkK3dActHosoqhg1ncF-Jy8aN3mQ-l15oaVcBEQbgbW8K3NZ13BqVVLJq3XzW3N-56grlH0z_snjd6Y4eZ8mGrPt8gLOJicrwBpnqPwfTXPfJ9O3YzYuEV13xzumwJKYtD8aFl6R7-4E-UdthmotUBM5g_KC3mnq_Mpm"
      title: "stackoverflow.com"
    }
    summary: "The `forms.googleapis.com/v1/forms` endpoint is part of the Google Forms API, which allows programmatic interaction with Google Forms. Specifically, to access form responses, you\'ll utilize the `v1.forms.responses` REST resource[1].\n\nHere\'s a breakdown of how to work with Google Forms responses using the API:\n*   **API Overview**: The Google Forms API enables you to read and write Google Forms and their responses. The base URL for the REST API is `https://forms.googleapis.com`[1][2].\n*   **Retrieving Responses**:\n    *   To get a list of all responses for a form, you use the `forms.responses.list` method, providing the `formId` in the URL[3][4]. The API will return a list of response objects in the \"responses\" field[2].\n    *   To retrieve a specific response, you can call the `forms.responses.get` method, which requires both the `formId` and the `responseId`[3][4][5]. The URL structure for this request is `GET https://forms.googleapis.com/v1/forms/{formId}/responses/{responseId}`[5]. The response body will contain an instance of `FormResponse`[5].\n*   **`FormResponse` Resource**: A `FormResponse` object contains details such as the form ID, response ID, submission timestamps, and the actual answers to questions, keyed by `question_id`[6][7]. If the form was a quiz and graded, it also includes the total score[7].\n*   **Authentication and Authorization**:\n    *   All requests to the Google Forms API require a Bearer (OAuth 2.0) access token[2].\n    *   You need to enable the Google Forms API in the Google Cloud Console for your project[8][2].\n    *   OAuth credentials (client ID and client secret) must be created, and the access token should have appropriate Forms API scopes, such as `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/forms.responses.readonly` for reading responses[2][5].\n*   **Key Use Cases**: The API supports creating and editing forms, as well as reacting to form responses for automations like real-time dashboards or triggering workflows[4].\n*   **Important Note**: The Google Forms API is currently designed for managing forms and retrieving responses, not for programmatically submitting user-supplied questionnaire responses directly through the API itself. However, if form responses are saved to a Google Sheet, you might be able to use the Google Sheets API to send in data[9].\n\nSources:\n[1] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF6kC0rEBAWkCmTQdwQ1u68ohtBxc1E6rIc6DkVxqBgB7NOF8ENDtylKWElMCaCll-fjJPy2NLXXjVeSAVfceGD6H53w6puCGTuOsX4znSw35_I8AnqKu2ozDbrb4YYI6p2ugjvCwI5x4leO2q8bf7uWuis9AKX8Up5gQ==)\n[2] [dlthub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8G_xAJmpz5j6j2OBuWXkIkx3T9UHhdf4KHZsj9zzp_njiKFdJJbTF8veFIz9bQbnDV1uqB2lBRPtxowGv4U-QOqNrHl0VTrBFlTtSiaLAAq1hV1HydZXLHuf-4Oit9M4AD6qts36lJQ==)\n[3] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQErE502X5UpDuxAjpndPlbNgcT7Tq7Tc7jVvhb_HcI0Kq_SOvTBsVuulmWsS2ZQjWqsD5tuQG7E7eVHWykC7sUrHjQYem5s2WJjgB-jcTIT_z9MvoWITPIEa5-IZd2kF8LyPIEdMqSQ_qS7JPOxl1S_wdga1tTrrzf4dMlK4fQG80Ll06Z-0MlP_51c)\n[4] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHPoKaoVzsKr5h-U2YWG9nTCO5O58O8qMsWdMJ2jWvfOCV3Pbee_WXL1xSF7MMnNndIpsQ9J9YSd_aLObQvzKWjTbgT-2EpB3oLIRkRrkjHQBQ0ccbPKYUDpxHo_2a3QrHq59sHKg==)\n[5] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFyadkc5e8F43TeCM7Tc2fPgc2axcm2FCpxqdK4E9bommoymlUJjzLENaT2382g_1ATU2zsQoSmIJChuSTdj-el6mO2lwDhpR2WcNnmuH0iBFPWFTAAddBB9g3i5PIf42_rLwUxTu1rHS4UXzEGJXEy_gWO3OHvj6NtnlRlsX0tmHQWEqM8mZ0LzDrpYyrOYMWn)\n[6] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFsEWLrQdtqGjrocQxDIh40iszRta91YebqUD9QU_9lv-Nu9WJtwDRV7VsgwMLqnIHKlCI63YFRh1B1AT1X_p0ktDjH8YaozYDoYnprHICNyud55DXyXUBQajJW5tOHjlbXlQ0p_vtM9NivvOqHMGdhFsd4F9db1y9uZ8SqBSQzB4FBNs-pa-kOAXSDqS4=)\n[7] [googleapis.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGul_dxafXI4M0K67lCEKgauxamoXb7LUfdxJe1iXZ1RnzOprBUPA9rQR2-YuyDv_GgMH5eq9hYHD4ThNiTUtkVGpcRuAdUXL1dfwHBieOQLOwBbEFEMBI2yBDQY8AuxYu4gPfMF2cEVWr4HRmSEr0lorln2WTWMadSqrsC0xn_uiUk_t8rBBTKTrT-vERpH2FBJBviFwwdF_EtlrJriUMmNuMW)\n[8] [endgrate.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFm5w_s7JGKigfS-GLTkbEgDHzpdxAHGIyVXT_f2z25IWOwMrfbYgKPjmOlRDB_L6XQCaHt2VBH9MyH6rtT1eRUr4kbeQpCqt14WbEJIb12tqoVPwubRhF4tn5ubKLw8K-2PvTck2af9GzionRauNCPoUD6bv1H-BPMFQ56gyrKBo7WcjhAxeOCP5p90MVQbtk=)\n[9] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFoC3HdMFn69mBn1tvRjz2-weihWvlX__X_CYtHID4TlbN_kkK3dActHosoqhg1ncF-Jy8aN3mQ-l15oaVcBEQbgbW8K3NZ13BqVVLJq3XzW3N-56grlH0z_snjd6Y4eZ8mGrPt8gLOJicrwBpnqPwfTXPfJ9O3YzYuEV13xzumwJKYtD8aFl6R7-4E-UdthmotUBM5g_KC3mnq_Mpm)"
    search_type: SEARCH_WEB_TYPE_WEB
