    summary: "The string \"1FAIpQL\" often appears within the URL of a Google Form, specifically as part of the form\'s identifier when the form is in \"view\" or \"prefill\" mode. It is typically found after `/d/e/` in the URL (e.g., `https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQL.../viewform`). While this string is part of the form\'s unique address, the actual `formId` used with the Google Forms API is a distinct value found in the edit URL of a form, located between `https://docs.google.com/forms/d/` and `/edit`[1][2].\n\nThe Google Forms API is a RESTful interface that enables developers to programmatically interact with Google Forms. Its functionalities include:\n*   **Creating and Modifying Forms and Quizzes** You can build new forms or quizzes and update existing ones[1][3].\n*   **Retrieving Form Responses and Quiz Grades** The API allows you to access submitted responses and quiz grades[1][4].\n*   **Setting Up Quiz Answer Keys** You can configure answer keys with automatic feedback for quizzes[1].\n*   **Receiving Push Notifications** The API supports push notifications for form schema changes or new response submissions[1][3].\n*   **Reading Form Content and Metadata** You can access the structure and details of a form[1][4].\n\nCommon applications of the Google Forms API involve automating form generation from data sources, creating real-time dashboards for response data, and triggering business workflows based on submitted information[3].\n\nIt\'s important to note that the Google Forms API is primarily designed for managing the form document itself and retrieving responses. Currently, it does not support programmatically submitting responses to a form through the API[5]. For submitting data, alternative methods such as using the Google Sheets API (if the form responses are linked to a Google Sheet) or Google Apps Script might be considered[5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEzWSoezGSEfPWQD5Kw4XUfNqmSbTpwK7ESqxRISb1QpS8S4pufBkEwDRfUmAwLnAtUhstDPE_MPdspxj9aJoB-9BB-ubPHJjgwtPmcgOhxJqA91jDZ-2cQNxpWleS_mrBsqhmC6-jFSsVAUh36Vn__GCrf)\n[2] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHrgM7QZU3BrExXir81ROMKGjSpNSB1PM1wJzbBWOhwOpOQjY9C9Fbphx1BoPNEwACuHva75av8Mx695EraDmrUrHV5WeXISGl8nIvUzPQTxmxTLitlrEX9PqTLJtZTk0fuwYap6cOPZiQEKPXynHLapxZ4kXGOfbyJ6Nh2tsdfehuu)\n[3] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFzpjF2sb9txMYsYYbc_C-foX5FjmZqn-UvidBN7tcN9hlXkq_l4AeiVtQnhntw8Z03HxhXJFYyVzxabZZcQXo_o5pV1kC8C_rWVp0I3ApNYC6jRBeNcOajLv3_-ZmmQ0_HKp1RVDo=)\n[4] [dlthub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGBUSQdmg2ZHwm8kVvOBy90HGY7u_Bz5cjHeZho1fvFw3MXwkmlAsfO2hiuUWiQh_d_LWzfEsI56vls-vlcDDiMx-XCS2X4Lef4Ikcu1Z4z9jtckNMULW1p6Nk84X5BF_JM3EfIEy_ePCU=)\n[5] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEgqpiHA7uDY830tWikAO6AYQjgEYteHRl5RQIu-vATuGLf5Ps2hB6_NtchZk_CcU8TQfLIhyrGWDzyoBrv5hl_TrLma3m2alMJwZUM1tpaV_IEH3Gj-AtmkCPqeIpcgcAdr4CuK99IFvH22WsTwQAF0-ImGVc-hRJ9hyjegVw-rbNPj8komLS74L6U68d75YK750y7f0cTynjpsKWvIg==)"
    search_type: SEARCH_WEB_TYPE_WEB
