      title: "google.com"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEeiGylJST0qLGOLsfamid65BCBvJhrr_V3eKgIkyMFGYfrZ4ZPXevkYSxls61D0RupKckqGRxMwxjRDIa1HgTBFyu67qzhIoMSqazS22e9s3d-94g3yGow3DdtGSKOkOne4tO93NB8O0A="
      title: "dlthub.com"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG98trZdrn1oF2kouEPXPTf0icfPYApDoaIWtJqJFRpuydlsLs7LFPildwpudXlFNXky25MteugMIYIN1akZa19K7hBoj4cDG44HZ4K12UqRwBYKq0YKA8meYhsd3k0VcFe3Yel45R-XxbV1cHmeDXJndjdFgTz1WWtzuRJSSRn9pglwn3ldz-9zpsO-Z532qJGxp7UMgaCT1E="
      title: "stackoverflow.com"
    }
    summary: "The `formId` in the Google Forms API is a unique identifier for each Google Form, comprising letters, numbers, hyphens, or underscores. This ID is an essential component when interacting with the Google Forms API to perform actions such as retrieving form details, updating a form, or accessing responses[1][2][3].\n\nWhen a Google Forms URL contains a string like `\"1FAIpQL\"`, this prefix is part of the `formId` itself. The entire string of characters found after `/d/` in the form\'s URL constitutes the complete `formId`[1]. For example, in a URL like `https://docs.google.com/forms/d/FORM_ID/edit`, `FORM_ID` represents the full form identifier[1].\n\nTo use the Google Forms API, you typically need to:\n*   **Obtain the `formId`**: This can be directly extracted from the Google Forms URL when viewing or editing a form[1].\n*   **Authenticate**: The Google Forms API requires OAuth 2.0 for authentication. This involves creating a project in the Google Cloud Console, enabling the Google Forms API, and configuring OAuth 2.0 client IDs or service accounts. You must also grant the necessary scopes, such as `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/forms.responses.readonly` for reading responses[3].\n*   **Make API calls**: Once authenticated, the `formId` is used in API requests. For instance, to retrieve a form, you would use an endpoint like `GET /v1/forms/{formId}`. To list responses, the endpoint would be `GET /v1/forms/{formId}/responses`[2][3].\n\nWhile there isn\'t a direct method within the Forms API to list all available forms, the Google Drive API\'s `Files: list` method can be used. By querying with `mimeType = \'application/vnd.google-apps.form\'`, you can find Google Forms stored in Drive, which would allow you to identify their respective `formId` values[4].\n\nIt is important to ensure the `formId` is valid and that the authenticated user or service account has appropriate access permissions to the form in Google Drive; otherwise, API requests may result in a 404 error[3].\n\nSources:\n[1] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHKbVN-i4agPr-KWAoPlsdl74s_pIVYF7ZhBEdKQNBjmTqtSGBlyEuVGmRlfxg-4G6ki7z68jjrHx-pNMjx0K2l2D_b34WOk6cDcba-XqS_nOy0aG4BH8W0Rpzn4TRzr_T_gA7NmBNesKvz-4I3J6CXfxdP)\n[2] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGJLb2Gnm6alJ6VUpxs7AmCj4JXcz_wYduW7i0svplPAcUXg6nxRbDDhKh7hwy1SsvsctkdqO3BOFEzlxVn7YBreKTZALoe43RRfrT4KYMfKuLWdT3Xj68uYp7nRVbQ9P6tIOCGz65XJvs4vjpDb5DZn91KqwQw8B7fcuM=)\n[3] [dlthub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEeiGylJST0qLGOLsfamid65BCBvJhrr_V3eKgIkyMFGYfrZ4ZPXevkYSxls61D0RupKckqGRxMwxjRDIa1HgTBFyu67qzhIoMSqazS22e9s3d-94g3yGow3DdtGSKOkOne4tO93NB8O0A=)\n[4] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG98trZdrn1oF2kouEPXPTf0icfPYApDoaIWtJqJFRpuydlsLs7LFPildwpudXlFNXky25MteugMIYIN1akZa19K7hBoj4cDG44HZ4K12UqRwBYKq0YKA8meYhsd3k0VcFe3Yel45R-XxbV1cHmeDXJndjdFgTz1WWtzuRJSSRn9pglwn3ldz-9zpsO-Z532qJGxp7UMgaCT1E=)"
