        markdown_chunk {
          headers {
            type: MARKDOWN_NODE_TYPE_HEADER_1
            text: "[How can I use Tailwind in React to animate a div to fill out its length from left to right](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75171765/how-can-i-use-tailwind-in-react-to-animate-a-div-to-fill-out-its-length-from-lef)"
          }
          text: "[How can I use Tailwind in React to animate a div to fill out its length from left to right](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75171765/how-can-i-use-tailwind-in-react-to-animate-a-div-to-fill-out-its-length-from-lef)\n[Ask Question](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/ask)\n[3 years, 4 months ago](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75171765/accessing-published-google-form-via-api?lastactivity)\nThis is an example of the divs, I just want to them to grow from left to right. Is this possible in Tailwind in React?\n- [css](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/css)\n- [reactjs](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/reactjs)\n- [tailwind-css](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tailwind-css)\n[css](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/css)\n[reactjs](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/reactjs)\n[tailwind-css](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tailwind-css)\n[Share](https://stackoverflow.com/q/75171765)\n[Improve this question](https://stackoverflow.com/posts/75171765/edit)\n[kmurp62rulz](https://stackoverflow.com/users/9828634/kmurp62rulz)\n- \n\n\n                    1\n\n\n\n\n\n                Yup, you can do that. Tailwind not providing any classes for this so you have to use logic to achieve this.\n\n\n                    [Sahil Ardeshna](https://stackoverflow.com/users/11112388/sahil-ardeshna)\n\342\200\223\302\240\n                        Sahil Ardeshna\n\n                2023-01-19 11:56:42 +00:00\n\n                    Commented\n                    Jan 19, 2023 at 11:56\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n- \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n- \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                Could you provide an example of how I could use logic to achieve this?\n\n\n                    [kmurp62rulz](https://stackoverflow.com/users/9828634/kmurp62rulz)\n\342\200\223\302\240\n                        kmurp62rulz\n\n                2023-01-21 00:43:54 +00:00\n\n                    Commented\n                    Jan 21, 2023 at 0:43\n\n\n\n\n- \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                Please share your example then i will update it as per your request.\n\n\n                    [Sahil Ardeshna](https://stackoverflow.com/users/11112388/sahil-ardeshna)\n\342\200\223\302\240\n                        Sahil Ardeshna\n\n                2023-01-22 02:55:35 +00:00\n\n                    Commented\n                    Jan 22, 2023 at 2:55\n\n\n\n\n[Sahil Ardeshna](https://stackoverflow.com/users/11112388/sahil-ardeshna)\n[kmurp62rulz](https://stackoverflow.com/users/9828634/kmurp62rulz)\n[Sahil Ardeshna](https://stackoverflow.com/users/11112388/sahil-ardeshna)\n[Add a comment](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75171765/accessing-published-google-form-via-api)"
        }
      }
