          text: "## 1 Answer 1\n[Reset to default](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75171765/how-can-i-use-tailwind-in-react-to-animate-a-div-to-fill-out-its-length-from-lef?answertab=scoredesc#tab-top)\nYou can achieve this but it needs additional css file\n\n```\ncss\n```\n\n\n#### Example:\nanimation.css\n\n```\nanimation.css\n```\n\n\n```\n@keyframes fill-left-to-right { from { width: 0; } to { width: 100%; } } .fill-left-to-right { animation: fill-left-to-right 1s ease-in-out; }\n```\n\n\n```\n@keyframes fill-left-to-right { from { width: 0; } to { width: 100%; } } .fill-left-to-right { animation: fill-left-to-right 1s ease-in-out; }\n```\n\nComponent.js\n\n```\nComponent.js\n```\n\n\n```\nimport \'./animation.css\' return ( <div className=\"fill-left-to-right\"> {/* Your content here */} </div> )\n```\n\n\n```\nimport \'./animation.css\' return ( <div className=\"fill-left-to-right\"> {/* Your content here */} </div> )\n```\n\nYou can do this for every div specifying different class and changing the width prop of that custom class\n\n```\ndiv\n```\n\n\n```\nwidth\n```\n\n[Share](https://stackoverflow.com/a/75230122)\n[Improve this answer](https://stackoverflow.com/posts/75230122/edit)\n[krishnaacharyaa](https://stackoverflow.com/users/13431819/krishnaacharyaa)\n\n## Comments\nAdd a comment\n\n## Your Answer\nThanks for contributing an answer to Stack Overflow!\n- Please be sure to answer the question. Provide details and share your research!\nBut avoid \342\200\246\n- Asking for help, clarification, or responding to other answers.\n- Making statements based on opinion; back them up with references or personal experience.\nTo learn more, see our [tips on writing great answers](https://stackoverflow.com/help/how-to-answer)."
        }
      }
