  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Google Forms Manager**\n\nI\'ve successfully created the Firebase auth file! Now, I\'m diving into designing `/src/components/GoogleFormsManager.tsx`. I\'m starting to think about the necessary API calls to fetch Google Forms responses, specifically starting with `GET https://forms.googleapis.com/v1/forms/{formId}` to retrieve form information like items and title.\n\n\n**Defining Google Forms Types**\n\nI\'m now deep in defining the TypeScript types for Google Forms. I\'ve structured `FormInfo` and `FormItem`, considering fields like `title`, `description`, and the nested `questionItem` with its relevant details, including question ID, required status, and various question types. I am also working on `FormResponse`, focusing on `responseId`, timestamps, and the structure of `answers`, mapping `questionId` to a `QuestionResponse` object. I am checking the form of `textAnswers`.\n\n\n**Auto-Mapping Google Form Questions**\n\nI\'m working on auto-mapping Google Form questions to my database fields. I\'ve sketched out a `defaultMapping` object and am creating a function to analyze question titles within `formInfo.items`. I\'m using keyword matching (\"name,\" \"title,\" \"style,\" etc.) to automatically link questions to the correct database properties like `clientName`, `title`, and others. This mapping should streamline data entry significantly.\n\n\n**Refining Automated Question Mapping**\n\nI\'ve refined the automated question mapping. Now, if a question title includes terms like \"dimension,\" \"size,\" or \"print size,\" I\'m mapping it to the `dimensions` field. Similarly, titles containing \"note,\" \"remark,\" or \"instruction\" are mapped to `notes`. I\'m aiming for the \"Wow, it just worked!\" moment. I\'m considering scenarios with active responses, especially those involving file uploads, and how to handle Google Drive file IDs and offer upload options. If a file ID or URL appears in a response, I can auto-populate the intake modal and let them upload, use a demo, or download the photo (if possible).\n\n\n**Visualizing the User Interface**\n\nI\'m now focusing on designing the user interface. I\'ve sketched out the initial components: a Google Account Status section with login/logout options, a Form Source Setup area with URL input and a sync button, and a Question Mapping Schema. The UI will show a prominent \"Connect Google Workspace Forms\" card with a \"Sign in with Google\" button if not signed in; otherwise, it will display a \"Connected as\" status and Sign Out option. I\'ve included a text input prepopulated with the form URL and a sync button with a loader, alongside a helper for finding the editable Form ID.\n\n\n**Designing Submission Visualization**\n\nI\'m now designing the Submissions / Responses Feed. I envision a card list showing submission order, time, and mapped parameters (like Client, Title, Style). Each card will include an \"Import Spec to Production\" button that pre-fills the artwork intake form. I\'m considering both opening the standard intake form and a direct-import option for maximum flexibility.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the Google Forms Management component at `/src/components/GoogleFormsManager.tsx`. This component handles the actual OAuth sign-in flow, extracts the Form ID from standard view or edit URLs, queries the Google Forms API for questions and submissions, auto-maps the question answers to portrait fields (Client Name, Artwork Title, Frame, treatment style, etc.), and imports those submissions directly into the IndexedDB Production Workspace."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 861754566
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
