  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Tab Navigation**\n\nI\'m exploring tab navigation. I initially thought this was perfect, but now I\'m considering integrating tab display directly within `App.tsx`! I\'ve been pondering if switching active tabs would make it simpler to integrate with the user flow. Specifically, I realized we can probably omit the \"Dynamic Controls Bar\" for `\'google-forms\'` tabs, because it\'s tab-specific.\n\n\n**Refining Tab Placement**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on integrating the tab bar directly into `App.tsx`, immediately above the `<main>` element, specifically around lines 212-235. I\'m focusing on crafting a seamless toggle between \"Production Workspace\" (including the Roster and Workstation Review) and a new \"Google Intake Forms Hub.\" My immediate challenge is determining the optimal placement of the tab buttons within this section. Also, should we display the \"Dynamic Header\" search input and filter chips for the `\'google-forms\'` tab?\n\n\n**Integrating Tab Display**\n\nI\'m now thinking about integrating tab display into `Header.tsx` to handle tab selection. I\'m considering conditionally displaying or hiding the search/filter section in `Header` based on the active tab. Adding tab buttons right next to the path navigation, or even beside the \"+ Upload Photo\" button in `Header` looks like a clean design approach! I\'m trying to decide the best location within the `Header.tsx` structure for these tab buttons.\n\n\n**Refining Tab Implementation**\n\nI\'m now contemplating further refinement of tab implementation. I\'m leaning toward incorporating the tab selector as a sub-header within `Header.tsx`, either just above the stats or the main content. This would avoid complex changes, and I\'m thinking of how to introduce `activeTab` and `setActiveTab` as props within `HeaderProps`, which is a clean solution. I\'m focusing on the sub-header segment now. Also, when `activeTab` is set to `\'workspace\'`, I want to display the dynamic controls bar and stats, whilst conditionally hiding them.\n\n\n**Evaluating Tab Positioning**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on positioning tabs! Since Google Forms has its own search, hiding the local roster search is ideal. I\'m considering placing tab navigation below the title, near the \"+ Upload Photo\" button, or as full horizontal tabs in the header. I\'m assessing the best placement within the title block, specifically near the pathway navigation. Also, I\'m thinking whether to incorporate the Google Forms tab search.\n\n\n**Finalizing Tab Display**\n\nI\'ve hit on something fantastic! Integrating tabs into the breadcrumb-style navigation is clean and elegant, perfect for a subtle interface. I can also add large, tactile tabs below the title. This allows for discoverability and a professional feel, which is the best of both worlds. I\'m focusing on making this a seamless experience.\n\n\n**Implementing Tab Navigation**\n\nI\'m now implementing the tab bar directly within the header, above the stats. I\'ve designed simple styled buttons for \"Production Desk\" and \"Google Forms,\" each with an active state. My immediate focus is integrating this functionality and ensuring smooth switching between tabs. I\'m keen on how this integration will improve the overall user experience!\n\n\n\n**Refining Tab Styling**\n\nI\'m now refining the tab styling, and I think I\'ve cracked it. Standard horizontal tabs with an active bottom border aligns perfectly with modern dashboard designs. I\'m focusing on positioning the tab bar below the brand block in the header to clearly separate the brand from the stats/controls. My current thoughts revolve around conditional rendering: displaying the Stats Board and Dynamic Controls Bar for the \'workspace\' tab, but only showing the Stats Board for the \'google-forms\' tab, since dynamic controls don\'t apply.\n\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to edit `/src/components/Header.tsx` to include an elegant Tab Navigation Bar and conditionally render Roster-specific search filters depending on whether the active workspace tab is \"Production Desk\" or \"Google Forms Sync Hub\". This provides a modern, clean full-view tabbed interface."
